          "type": "text",
          "heading": "The simple version",
          "body": "The stack feels simple because the lifetime is tied to the function call. Heap allocation starts making sense when the value needs to survive outside that neat stack frame story, or when its size / ownership pattern does not fit nicely on the stack."
